ChatGPT said:

server.js almost JavaScript async/await mistake error

Problem:

js
const app = createServer(); //   `async function`

await already await , top-level await ESM modules (type: module) allow

Fix: Use an Async IIFE (Immediately Invoked Function Expression)

:

js
// server/server.js
import { createServer } from "./createServer.js";
import connectDB from "./db.js";
import dotenv from "dotenv";

dotenv.config();

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 4000;

(async () => {
  try {
    await connectDB(); //  ensure DB connected

    const app = await createServer(); //  wait for createServer()

    app.listen(PORT, () => {
      console.log(` Server running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);
    });
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(" Server startup failed:", err.message);
    process.exit(1);
  }
})();

Advantages:

  • async error

  • Port startup handle

  • Future stable structure
